c finite-predicate-v0 forall-implies-exists-finite
c Variables encode the unary predicate over U = {a,b}: P(a)=1 and P(b)=2.
c Clauses 1 and 2 assert forall x. P(x). Clauses -1 and -2 assert that
c exists x. P(x) fails. The finite universe is non-empty, so these constraints
c are contradictory.
p cnf 2 4
1 0
2 0
-1 0
-2 0
